==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Strobilation
<hw>Strob`i*la"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>The act or phenomenon of spontaneously dividing transversely, as do
certain species of annelids and helminths; transverse fission. See
<xex>Illust.</xex> under <er>Syllidian</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Strobile</ent>⟦br⟧
